<l>tiṅkaṇ muṉvari ṉikkē cāriyai</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If the [names of] the months precede [a verb], <foreign xml:lang="ta">ikku</foreign> is the empty-morph.<note place="foot">E.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṭikkuppōyiṉāṉ.</foreign> Names of months <foreign xml:lang="ta">(tiṅkaḷ)</foreign> ended in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-i</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ai (287).</foreign> In the earliest strata of Tamil texts, we find
          the following : <foreign xml:lang="ta">tai (Kuṟ. 196.4), māci (Patiṟṟup. 59.2), paṅkuṉi (Puṟam 229.5), cittirai (Cilapp. 5.64), āṭi (Cilapp. 23.133).</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
